# Seimas Open Data Endpoint Policy

Source of truth: `https://www.lrs.lt/sip/portal.show?p_r=35391&p_k=1`

- Do not use non-official endpoints for ingestion.
- `p2b.ad_sn_kalbos` is not official and must not be used.
- Before changing ingest logic, verify endpoint existence against the official list.

## Official endpoints to use

- MP members: `p2b.ad_seimo_nariai`
- MP initiated bills: `p2b.ad_sn_inicijuoti_ta_projektai`
- MP bill proposals: `p2b.ad_sn_pasiulymai_ta_projektams`
- MP press releases (speech proxy): `p2b.ad_sn_pranesimai_ziniasklaidai`
- MP schedules: `p2b.ad_sn_darbotvarkes`
- MP business trips: `p2b.ad_sn_komandiruotes`
- Session proceedings: `p2b.ad_sp_eiga`
- Full session flow: `p2b.ad_seimo_posedzio_eiga_full`

## Speech-data strategy

- Preferred communication proxy: `p2b.ad_sn_pranesimai_ziniasklaidai`.
- Alternative for embedded speech extraction: `p2b.ad_seimo_posedzio_eiga_full`.
- If using proxy metrics, label them clearly as proxy in code/API responses.

## Query constraints

- Prefer per-MP calls when supported (use `?asmens_id=...`) to avoid global aggregates.
- Keep ingestion parsers schema-aware and resilient to missing XML fields.
